My meme

In my meme, I used two online images and two images I created myself. It shows my anticipation and love for statistics.

library(magick)

# read image from online and assign name with "meme".

meme <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2021/01/13/03/27/heart-5913128_960_720.png") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# second online image that I use and assign name with "meme_2".

meme_2 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2020/12/14/15/48/light-bulb-5831252_960_720.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# third online image that I use and assign name with "meme_3".

meme_3 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/02/17/16/09/heart-1205291__340.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(300)
  
# fourth online image that I use and assign name with "meme_4".
  
meme_4 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/01/09/10/48/heart-1966017__340.png")%>%
  image_scale(300)

# fifth online image that I use and assign name with "meme_5".

meme_5 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2018/04/04/14/45/design-3289984__340.png")%>%
  image_scale(300)

# create a new image and assign name with "image", and add text in the image.
  
image <- image_blank(width = 300,    # size
                    height = 300,   # size
                    color = "#ffffe6") %>%        # filling color
  image_annotate(text = "Love\nStatistics",        # text content
                   color = "#1a53ff",          # text color
                   size = 50,                  # text size
                   font = "Impact",            # text font
                   gravity = "center")         # text location
  
# create second image and assign name with "image_2", and add text on it.
  
image_2 <- image_blank(width = 300,    # size
                      height = 300,     # size
                      color = "#ffffe6") %>%    # filling color
  image_annotate(text = "Love to work",          # text content
                   color = "#ff0066",      # text color
                   size = 50,              # text size
                   font = "Impact",        # text font
                   gravity = "center")     # text location
  
# create third image and assign name with "image_3", and add text on it.
  
image_3 <- image_blank(width = 300,    # size
                        height = 300,     # size
                        color = "#ffffe6") %>%    # filling color
    image_annotate(text = "Go for it",          # text content
                   color = "#33cc33",      # text color
                   size = 50,              # text size
                   font = "Impact",        # text font
                   gravity = "center")     # text location
  
# create fourth image and assign name with "image_4", and add text on it.
  
image_4 <- image_blank(width = 300,    # size
                       height = 300,     # size
                       color = "#ffffe6") %>%    # filling color
  image_annotate(text = "Keep it up",          # text content
                  color = "#ff8c1a",      # text color
                  size = 50,              # text size
                  font = "Impact",        # text font
                  gravity = "center")     # text location

# first row

first_row <- c(meme, image, meme_3) %>%
  image_append()

# second row

second_row <- c(image_2, meme_2, image_3) %>%
  image_append()

# third row

third_row <- c(meme_4, image_4, meme_5)%>%
  image_append()

# combine first row and second row.
final <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# save my image
image_write(final, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

In my GIF, I used online picture and one images I created myself. It shows many kind of food.

library(magick)

# load image
buger <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/174808500/photo/burger-with-potato-chips.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=hi3IgVrmGCTMt0UJOu3Ll0NvEfZozzWWKhs9g90CMp0=") %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

cake <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/01/11/11/33/cake-1971552__340.jpg") %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

pizza <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/04/28/21/20/pizza-744405__340.jpg") %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

donuts <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/08/30/11/31/candy-2696734__340.jpg") %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

kfc <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1158156755/photo/crispy-chicken-drumsticks-grilled-kfc-style-with-crackers.jpg?b=1&s=170667a&w=0&k=20&c=SVg1kxkhKFSlWq81pp_02jXYEPnHpY6NQXDZRyt4a5k=") %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

# create image
image <- image_blank(width = 500,    # size
                     height = 500,   # size
                     color = "#0077b3") %>%        # filling color
  image_annotate(text = "What is your \n favorite food",        # text content
                 color = "#99ddff",          # text color
                 size = 70,                  # text size
                 font = "Impact",            # text font
                 gravity = "center")         # text location

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(image, buger, cake, pizza, donuts, kfc)

# creating an animation
  image_animate(frames, fps = 1)
